{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Brioche","content":["Lightly grease a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and set aside.","Place milk into mixing bowl and warm <b>1 min\/37°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add sugar, yeast and butter and warm <b>2 min\/37°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add flour, salt and eggs and mix <b>6 sec\/speed 6<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then knead <b>4 min\/<b>.","Transfer dough onto a silicone bread mat or lightly floured work surface and knead dough by hand until it isn't sticky. Shape into a ball and place into thermal serving bowl or other large bowl. Cover with a kitchen towel and leave to prove in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 1 hour). Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Preheat oven to 180°C. Line a pizza tray (30 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Knock down dough, then transfer onto a silicone bread mat or lightly floured work surface. Knead dough a few times and shape into a log (approx. 25 cm). Flatten dough ball slightly and cut into 4 equal portions. Roll each portion into a ball.","Flatten each ball with your hand, then roll out dough portions into a circle (approx. 30 cm diameter, 3-4 mm thickness).","Place 1 dough circle onto prepared pizza tray and spread with ⅓ of the hazelnut chocolate spread, leaving a 1 cm edge. Place another dough circle on top of spread and cover with ⅓ of the hazelnut chocolate spread, leaving a 1 cm edge. Repeat with a third dough circle and remaining ⅓ hazelnut chocolate spread. Top with remaining dough circle and trim excess dough from edges.","Using a cooking cutter (5 cm) or the rim of a drinking glass, press lightly into centre of dough to make a light imprint.","Cut dough into quarters (do not cut through inner circle imprint). Cut each quarter in halves (do not cut through inner circle), creating 8 sections. Then cut each eighth into halves (do not cut through inner circle) - you will have a total of 16 sections.","Holding 2 neighbouring segments by the ends, twist outwards twice.. Pull ends together and pinch to seal. Repeat with remaining sections to create a total of 8 twisted portions. The brioche will look like a flower. Cover with plastic wrap. Leave to prove in a warm place for 20 minutes."]},{"title":"Glaze","content":["Place egg yolk and milk into mixing bowl and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 6<b>.","Lightly brush brioche with glaze. Bake for 20-25 minutes (180°C), until golden brown.","Allow to cool and dust with icing sugar (optional) before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Brioche","content":["oil, for greasing","180 g full cream milk","60 g white sugar","1 tsp dried yeast","60 g unsalted butter, melted","450 g baker's flour","1 tsp salt","2 eggs, lightly beaten","300 g hazelnut chocolate spread (see Tips)"]},{"title":"Glaze","content":["1 egg yolk","15 g full cream milk","icing sugar, to serve (optional)"]}],"id":"r107104","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-duv9SQZpxWo\/XZavCzs-KLI\/AAAAAAAAhqo\/rOenJvT71cM-N_9fq4KU3IpDo8cpJQuZwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_XoM67uRREax_Tnu6.png","title":"Hazelnut chocolate brioche","publishedAt":"2017-03-19T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.1 g","fat":"11.7 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"36.9 g","calories":"1161 kJ \/ 276 kcal"},"usefulItems":"thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, silicone bread mat, kitchen towel, pizza tray, baking paper, rolling pin, round cookie cutter (5 cm), plastic wrap, pastry brush, oven","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own hazelnut chocolate spread, please refer to the recipe in <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em>.","This recipe was contributed by Marshia Radin."],"basicInfo":["medium","40m","2h","16 portions"]}